== {{langue|en}} ==
=== {{S|étymologie}} ===
: De l’{{étyl|fro|mot=travail|sens=tourment, souffrance}}.

=== {{S|nom|en}} ===
{{en-nom|2=travails|p2=travaux|3=ˈtʁæ.veɪl|ps2=tɹə.ˈveɪl|4=ˈtʁæ.veɪlz|pp2=tɹə.ˈveɪlz|pp3=}}
'''travail''' {{pron|ˈtʁæ.veɪl|en}} ou {{pron|tɹə.ˈveɪl|en}}
# {{vieilli|en}} {{siècle|À partir du XIII}} [[effort|Effort]] [[pénible]] ou [[douloureux]] ; '''travail''' [[excessif]], [[souffrance]].
#* ''He had thought of making a destiny for himself, through laborious and untiring '''travail'''.'' {{source|{{w|Djuna Barnes}}, ''Nightwood'', 1936, Faber & Faber 2007, p. 38}}
# {{en particulier|en}} {{médecine|en}} [[douleur|Douleur]]s de l’[[accouchement]] ; [[#fr-nom-1|travail]].
# {{vieilli|en}} {{siècle|XIV|XVIII}} [[labeur|Labeur]], [[#fr-nom-1|travail]] ; acte de [[travailler]].
#* ''It was dark now. The sun was nearly set, and rain was starting to fall. Kelly headed south on York Road towards the city, well fed and relaxed himself, feeling confident and ready for the night’s '''travail'''.'' {{source|{{w|Tom Clancy}}, ''{{w|Sans aucun remords|Without Remorse}}'', 1993.}}
# {{vieilli|en}} {{siècle|XVII}} [[éclipse|Éclipse]] d’un objet céleste.
# {{vieilli|en}} {{variante de|travel|en}}.

